MuleSoft Anypoint Connector for Salesforce Data Cloud

Use MuleSoft Anypoint Connector for Salesforce Data Cloud to integrate data from any cloud or legacy systems to deliver personalized, connected, and relevant customer experiences.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience

Automate data ingestion from third-party sources by first setting up Ingestion API and then Mulesoft Anypoint Connector.

You can also query data to get new insights from Data Cloud using the query, profile, and calculated insights APIs. With MuleSoft Anypoint Connectors, you can:

Integrate systems 5x faster using pre-built connectors from Anypoint Exchange.
Connect to SaaS applications like SAP, Marketo, and Microsoft Dynamics 365.
Integrate with cloud infrastructure and services like Amazon Kinesis, Azure Data Lake Storage, and Azure Blob Storage.
Use JDBC and other open protocols to connect to data bases like Kafka, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB.
Authenticate easily when the JSON Web Token (JWT) expires.
Eliminate Data Cloud REST APIs by determining the CDP tenant-specific endpoint and paths to make requests based on the user’s configuration.
Build integration flows without custom code as MuleSoft provides many other connectors that can work with Salesforce MuleSoft Connector.
Salesforce Data Cloud Connector Use Cases

Connect your business applications with Data Cloud to unify profiles, segment unified data, activate, and analyze data. Use cases include:

Change data capture: Stream changes in records from the source system into Data Cloud in near-real-time using the Streaming Ingestion API.
Legacy integration: Schedule daily, weekly, or monthly loads of bulk exports from legacy systems using the Bulk Ingestion API.
Deliver a consistent, connected customer experience: Publish insights from Data Cloud into upstream systems like Salesforce CRM using the Query, Profile, or Calculated Insights APIs.
